                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. was rebound.
 The leather covering is probably
                           more recent then the boards, on which there are remains of another and
                           more ancient leather. Outer layers of the original leather covering (?)
                           are separated from the boards and loosely placed between the front board
                           and first folio and the back board and the last folio.
 Most of the
                           fols. are worn and affected by humidity.
 Stains on several fols.
                           (e.g., <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 39r, 71v, 71r, 89v, 90r, 197v,
                           198r).
 Holes or tears amended on some fols. (e.g. <locus target="#37">37</locus>, 53, 54, 70, 100, 143).</condition>
