                  <provenance>The name of the original commissioner has
                     been erased from the supplication formulas. However, on <locus target="#120ra">120ra</locus> and in the colophon, his name can still be decipherable as
                     Walda Giyorgis. In the supplication formula on <locus target="#42ra">42ra</locus>, the first part of his name (Walda) has not been erased; the
                     same, on some folios (e.g., <locus target="#42va">42va</locus>, 42vc), where
                     the last letter of his second name (-s) still remains. In some supplication
                     formulas his name has been replaced with the name of Za-Manfas Qǝddus (e.g.,
                     <locus target="#2ra">2ra</locus>, 5rb, 13vb, 57ra), written in red probably
                     in a different hand. Za-Manfas Qǝddus is the baptismal name of daǧǧāzmāč Subāgādis (1770-1831). In the supplication
                     formula on <locus target="#42ra">42ra</locus>, the name Lǝʿul is written over
                     erasure.</provenance>
